{"lemma":"أَصِيلَةٍ","slug":"أَصِيلَةٍ","root":"#.ص.ل","root_slug":"_-ص-ل","root_link":"/words/roots/_-ص-ل","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"أَصِيل","root":"أصل","pos":"N","occurrence_count":7},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":2,"pos_tags":["adj","name"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":4},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n887"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%A3%D9%8E%D8%B5%D9%90%D9%8A%D9%84%D9%8E%D8%A9%D9%8D"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"adj","gloss":"original, genuine, deep-rooted"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"noble"},{"pos":"adj","gloss":"purebred (horses, etc)"},{"pos":"name","gloss":"a male given name, Asil"}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"فَعِيل (faʕīl)-type stative-verb derived from the active participle from the verb أَصُلَ (ʔaṣula). Cognate with Hebrew אָצִיל (atsíl)."},"ipa":["/ʔa.sˤiːl/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n887","headword_ar":"اَصيلَةٌ","root":"ASl","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"A man's"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whole property:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(M, K:) or his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palm-trees:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K, TA: in the CK his"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"palmtree:"},{"kind":"text","text":") thus in the dial. of El-Hijáz. (O, TA.) ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axa*ahu biA^aSiylatihi","text_ar":"اَخَذَهُ بِاَصِيلَتِهِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, M, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"biA^aSalatihi","text_ar":"بِاَصَلَتِهِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, M, K,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He took it altogether,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M, K,) [as it were]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"with its root,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, M,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"not leaving aught of it."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) And"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaAw^uwA biA^aSiylatihimo","text_ar":"جَاوُوا بِاَصِيلَتِهِمْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"They came altogether; the whole of them."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Z.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lifulaAnK A^aroDN A^aSiylapN","text_ar":"لِفُلَانٍ اَرْضٌ اَصِيلَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To such a one belongs land long possessed, or inherited from his parents, by means of which he has his living:"},{"kind":"text","text":"a phrase of the people of Et-Táïf. (TA.)       -A3-  See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aSiylN","text_ar":"اَصِيلٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", in two places."}],"source_refs":["M","K","S","IAar"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}